President Barack Obama will posthumously award Staff Sergeant Robert J. Miller, U.S. Army, the Medal of Honor for his heroic actions in Afghanistan on January 25, 2008. Miller displayed immense courage and selflessness by sacrificing his own life to save his teammates and 15 Afghanistan National Army soldiers. His parents will join the President at the White House to commemorate their son's service and sacrifice. Miller enlisted in the United States Army in 2003 and became a Green Beret in 2005. He served as a weapons sergeant in Alpha Company, 3rd Battalion, 3rd Special Forces Group (Airborne). The Medal of Honor is awarded to members of the Armed Forces who demonstrate exceptional bravery and self-sacrifice above and beyond the call of duty.